1851283 11 The Chancellor.
950622 1The Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such manner as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
839507 2The Chancellor shall, by virtue of his office, be the Head of the University.
661376 3The Chancellor shall, if present, preside at the convocations of the University held for conferring degrees.
880343 12 The Vice- Chancellor.
430918 1The Vice- Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such manner as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
1560683 2The Vice- Chancellor shall be the principal executive and academic officer of the University, and shall exercise general supervision and control over the affairs of the University and give effect to the decisions of all the authorities of the University.
1730431 3The Vice- Chancellor may, if he is of opinion that immediate action is necessary on any matter, exercise any power conferred on any authority of the University by or under this Act and shall report to such authority the action taken by him on such matter: Provided that if the authority concerned is of opinion that such action ought not to have been taken, it may refer the matter to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final:
Provided further that any person in the service of the University who is aggrieved by the action taken by the Vice- Chancellor under this sub- section shall have the right to appeal against such action
219 1Subs. by Act 35 of 1989, s. 48 (w. e. f. 6- 9- 1994).
to the Executive Council within three months from the date on which decision on such action is communicated to him and thereupon the Executive Council may confirm, modify or reverse the action taken by the Vice- Chancellor.
1218941 4The Vice- Chancellor shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes or Ordinances.
1773208 13The Pro- Vice- Chancellors. Every Pro- Vice- Chancellor shall be appointed in such manner and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
1232410 14Deans of Schools. Every Dean of a School shall be appointed in such manner and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
1349664 15 The Registrar.
1595684 1The Registrar shall be appointed in such manner as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
1274061 2The Registrar shall have the power to enter into agreements, sign documents and authenticate records on behalf of the University and shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
137088 16The Finance Officer. The Finance Officer shall be appointed in such manner and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
908125 17Other officers. The manner of appointment and powers and duties of other officers of the University shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
512988 18 Authorities of the University. The following shall be the authorities of the University:-
1747270 1The Court;
804564 2The Executive Council;
1197047 3The Academic Council;
1948099 4The Boards of Schools; and
372629 5Such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be authorities of the University.
393935 19 The Court.
1955826 1The constitution of the Court and the term of office of its members shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
220
1841968 2Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Court shall have the following powers and functions, namely:-
174982 ato review, from time to time, the broad policies and programmes of the University and to suggest measures for the improvement and development of the University;
521940 bto consider and pass resolutions on the annual report and the annual accounts of the University and the audit report on such accounts;
683426 cto advise the Visitor in respect of any matter which may be referred to it for advice; and
804548 dto perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
1606765 20 The Executive Council.
1154121 1The Executive Council shall be the principal executive body of the University.
1047331 2The constitution of the Executive Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and duties shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
1573937 21 The Academic Council.
15213 1The Academic Council shall be the principal academic body of the University and shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and Ordinances, co- ordinate and exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University.
1574836 2The constitution of the Academic Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and duties shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
291110 22Other authorities of the University. The constitution, powers and functions of the Boards of Schools and of such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be authorities of the University, shall be prescribed by the Statutes.
512952 23 Planning Board.
796951 1There shall be constituted a Planning Board of the University which shall advise generally on the planning and development of the University and keep under review the standard of education and research in the University.
1044966 2The Planning Board shall consist of-
800388 aThe Vice- Chancellor, who shall be the Chairman, and
196312 bnot more than eight persons of high academic standing who shall be appointed in such manner as may be prescribed by the Statutes.
221
361928 3The Visitor may determine a date with effect from which the Planning Board shall stand dissolved.
401554 24 Power to make Statutes. Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:-
1505917 athe constitution, powers and functions of the authorities and other bodies of the University, as may be constituted from time to time;
