1034238 1In the case of Departments which have more than one Professor, the Head of the Department shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of the Vice- Chancellor from among the Professors.
166
1960951 2In the case of Departments where there is only one Professor, the Executive Council shall have the option to appoint, on the recom- mendation of the Vice- Chancellor, either the Professor or a Reader as the Head of the Department; Provided that it shall be open to a Professor or Reader to decline the offer of appointment as the Head of the Department.
484844 3A person appointed as the Head of the Department shall hold office as such for a period of three years and shall be eligible for reappointment.
1464890 4A Head of a Department may resign his office at any time during his tenure of office.
1460818 5A Head of a Department shall perform such functions as may be prescribed by the Ordinances.
1752110 8 Deans of Students' Welfare.
1499813 1Every Dean of Students' Welfare shall be appointed from amongst the teachers of the University, not below the rank of a Reader, by the Executive Council on the recommendation of the Vice- Chancellor.
1563788 2Every Dean appointed under clause (1) shall be a whole- time officer and shall hold office for a term of three years and shall be eligible for re- appointment: Provided that the Executive Council may, if it is considered necessary appoint, on the recommendation of the Vice- Chancellor, a teacher, not below the rank of a Reader, to discharge the duties of the Dean of Students' Welfare in addition to his duties as such teacher, and in such a case, the Executive Council may sanction a suitable allowance to be paid to him.
935408 3A person who is appointed as a Dean of Students' Welfare shall continue to hold his lien on his substantive post and shall be eligible to all the benefits that would have otherwise accrued to him, but for his appointment as the Dean of Students' Welfare.
1435333 4When the office of a Dean of Students' Welfare is vacant or when the Dean of Students' Welfare is, by reason of illness or absence or any other cause, unable to perform the duties of his office, the duties of the office shall be performed by such person as the Vice- Chancellor may appoint for the purpose.
278223 5The duties and powers of a Dean of Students' Welfare shall be prescribed by the Ordinances.
1702017 9 Proctors.
1994474 1Every Proctor shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of the Vice- Chancellor and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be assigned to him by the Vice- Chancellor.
882922 2Every Proctor shall hold office for a term of two years and shall be eligible for re- appointment.
1075936 10 Librarians.
240068 1Every Librarian shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of a Selection Committee constituted for the purpose and he shall be a whole- time officer of the University.
1997234 2Every Librarian shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be assigned to him by the Executive Council.
1851283 11 Meetings of the Court.
950622 1An annual meeting of the Court shall be held on a date to be fixed by the Executive Council unless some other date has been fixed by the Court in respect of any year.
167
839507 2At an annual meeting of the Court, a report on the working of the University during the previous year, together with a statement of the receipts and expenditure, the balance- sheet, as audited, and the financial estimates for the next year shall be presented.
661376 3A copy a the statement of receipts and expenditure, the balancesheet and the financial estimates referred to in clause (2) shall be sent to every member of the Court at least seven days before the date of the annual meeting.
1017965 4Twelve members of the Court shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Court.
1048023 5Special meetings of the Court may be convened by the Executive Council or the Vice- Chancellor, or, if there is no Vice- Chancellor, by a Pro- Vice- Chancellor, or if there is no Pro- Vice- Chancellor, by the Registrar.
880343 12Quorum for meetings of the Executive Council. Five members of the Executive Council shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Executive Council.
1773208 13 Powers and functions of Executive Council.
352934 1The Executive Council shall have the management and administration of the revenue and property of the University and the conduct of all administrative affairs of the University not otherwise provided for.
685003 2Subject to the provisions of this Act, these Statutes and the Ordinances, the Executive Council shall, in addition to. all other powers vested in it, have the following powers, namely:-
612179 ito create teaching and academic posts, to determine the number and emoluments of such posts and to define the duties and conditions of service of Professors, Readers, Lecturers and other academic staff and Principals of Colleges and Institutions maintained by the University: Provided that no action shall be taken by the Executive Council in respect of the number, qualifications and the emoluments of teachers and academic staff otherwise than after consideration of the recommendations of the Academic Council;
1763107 iito appoint such Professors, Readers, Lecturers and other academic staff, as may be necessary, and Principals of Colleges and Institutions maintained by the University on the recommendation of the Selection Committee constituted for the purpose and to fill up temporary vacancies therein;
1342502 iiito create administrative, ministerial and other necessary posts and to make appointments thereto in the manner prescribed by the Ordinances;
1619567 ivto grant leave of absence to any officer of the University, other than the Chancellor and the Vice- Chancellor, and to make necessary arrangements for the discharge of the functions of such officer during his absence;
1175888 vto regulate and enforce discipline among employees in accordance with these Statutes and the Ordinances:
168
1848203 vito manage and regulate the finances, accounts, investments, property, business and all other administrative affairs of the University, and for that purpose, to appoint such agents as it may think fit;
194231 viito fix limits on the total recurring and the total non- recurring expenditure for a year on the recommendations of the Finance Committee;
1636706 viiito invest any money belonging to the University, including any unapplied income, in such stocks, funds, shares or securities as it shall, from time to time, think fit, or in the purchase of immovable property in India, with the like powers of varying such investments from time to time;
1971188 ixto transfer or accept transfers of any movable or immov- able property on behalf of the University;
664227 xto provide buildings, premises, furniture and apparatus and other means needed for carrying on the work of the University;
79438 xito enter into, vary, carry out and cancel contracts on behalf of the University;
1884647 xiito entertain, adjudicate upon, and, if thought fit, to redress any grievances of the employees and students of the University, who may, for any reason feel aggrieved;
982234 xiiito appoint examiners and moderators and, if necessary to remove them, and to fix their fees, emoluments and travelling and other allowances, after consulting the Academic Council;
1176307 xivto select a common seal for the University and provide for the custody and use of such seal;
914097 xvto make such special arrangements as may be necessary for the residence and discipline of women students;
378019 xvito delegate any of its powers to the Vice- Chancellor, the Pro- Vice- Chancellors, the Registrar or the Finance Officer or such other employee or authority of the University or to a Committee appointed by It as it may deem fit;
1561474 xviito institute fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes; and
871586 xviiito exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed on it by this Act, or these Statutes.
1232410 14Quorum for meetings of the Academic Council. Nine members of the Academic Council shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Academic Council.
