1878553 ato exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University and to give directions regarding methods of
169
instruction, co- operative teaching among Colleges and Institutions, evaluation of research or improvements in academic standards;
1574471 bto bring about inter- School co- ordination, to establish or appoint Committees or Boards, for taking up projects on an inter- School basis;
1525111 cto consider matters of general academic interest either on its own initiative or on a reference by a School or the Executive Council and to take appropriate action thereon; and
1163317 dto frame such regulations and rules consistent with these. Statutes and the Ordinances regarding the academic functioning of the University, discipline, residences, admissions, award of fellowships and studentships, fee concessions, corporate life and, attendance.
